        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 6:54PM MDT by NWS North Platte NE</headline>
        <description>At 653 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 8 miles northwest of Hay Springs to 12 miles
northeast of Wild Horse Butte to 6 miles southwest of Alliance.
Movement was east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gordon, Rushville, Hay Springs, Ellsworth, Antioch, Clinton, Billys
Lake, Lone Butte, Intersection of Beaver Creek Road and White Clay
Creek Road, Intersection of Highway 87 and Larabee Road, Miles Lake,
Wickson Lake, Diamond Lake, Metcalf State Wildlife Management Area,
Herman Lake, Krause Lake, Watson Lake, Patterson Lake, Highway 27
crossing the Niobrara River, and Kennedy Lake.

This includes the following highways...
Highway 20 between mile markers 74 and 111.
Highway 250 between mile markers 1 and 48.
Highway 2 between mile markers 96 and 126.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
